</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="57" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,615,1379]" pageId="3" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,318,1198,1224]" pageId="3" pageNumber="57">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species is superficially similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[831,958,1199,1224]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macrotrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hamata" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[831,958,1199,1224]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="57">M. hamata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[965,1030,1198,1224]" pageId="3" pageNumber="57">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[965,1030,1198,1224]" pageId="3" pageNumber="57" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, but can be distinguished from the latter by: (
<number box="[279,292,1237,1263]" pageId="3" pageNumber="57" value="1.0">1</number>
) pygofer caudal process blunt; (
<number box="[685,701,1237,1263]" pageId="3" pageNumber="57" value="2.0">2</number>
) subapical process of style directed posteriorly; (
<number box="[1298,1313,1237,1263]" pageId="3" pageNumber="57" value="3.0">3</number>
) aedeagal shaft long and curved dorsally, narrowing to sharp apex. The new species is also similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Kuoh &amp; Cai" authorityName="Kuoh &amp; Cai" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Epiclinata" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavomarginata" status="n. comb.">
<emphasis box="[1217,1435,1276,1301]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="57">M. flavomarginata</emphasis>
(Kuoh &amp; Cai)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[319,424,1314,1340]" pageId="3" pageNumber="57">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[319,424,1314,1340]" pageId="3" pageNumber="57">n. comb.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, but can be distinguished from the latter by: (
<number box="[955,967,1314,1340]" pageId="3" pageNumber="57" value="1.0">1</number>
) aedeagus with paired processes arising dorsally; (
<number box="[270,286,1353,1379]" pageId="3" pageNumber="57" value="2.0">2</number>
) subapical process of style along inner margin unforked.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
